events.name: Missouri Tigers at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Broyles leads No. 1 Sooners' rally for 38-28 win

events.name: LSU Tigers at West Virginia Mountaineers

headlines.description: Jarrett Lee threw three touchdown passes, Michael Ford ran for two scores and No. 2 LSU made a case to be No. 1, beating No. 16 West Virginia 47-21 Saturday night.

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: Trent Richardson rushed for 120 yards and caught a 61-yard touchdown pass and No. 3 Alabama overwhelmed No. 14 Arkansas in a 38-14 win on Saturday.

events.name: Tulsa Golden Hurricane at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Kellen Moore tossed four touchdown passes, a pair to Tyler Shoemaker, in less than 2½ quarters, Jerrell Givens intercepted Tulsa quarterback G.J. Kinnie twice and No. 4 Boise State rolled to a 41-21 in its home opener on Saturday night.

events.name: South Dakota Coyotes at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: Nick Toon had a career-high 155 yards receiving and two touchdowns, helping No. 6 Wisconsin rout South Dakota 59-10 at Camp Randall Stadium on Saturday.

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Texas A&M Aggies

headlines.description: Brandon Weeden threw for a school-record 438 yards and two scores and Justin Blackmon and Josh Cooper combined for 244 yards receiving as No. 7 Oklahoma State rallied for a 30-29 win over No. 8 Texas A&M on Saturday.

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Wyoming Cowboys

venue.fullName: Jonah Field at War Memorial Stadium

headlines.description: No. 9 Nebraska beats Wyoming 38-14 behind Burkhead
headlines.shortLinkText: Burkhead helps No. 9 Nebraska best Wyoming

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Arizona Wildcats

headlines.description: No. 10 Oregon 56, Arizona 31

events.name: Florida State Seminoles at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd threw for three touchdowns and ran for another as No. 21 Clemson opened Atlantic Coast Conference play with a 35-30 victory over No. 11 Florida State on Saturday.

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at South Carolina Gamecocks

headlines.description: Marcus Lattimore scored two touchdowns and had 150 total yards from scrimmage to lead No. 12 South Carolina to a 21-3 win over Vanderbilt on Saturday night.

events.name: Virginia Tech Hokies at Marshall Thundering Herd

headlines.description: David Wilson rushed for 132 yards, Josh Oglesby scored two touchdowns and No. 13 Virginia Tech beat Marshall 30-10 on Saturday in a final tuneup before its anticipated Atlantic Coast Conference opener.

events.name: Florida Gators at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: Jeff Demps ran 10 times for 157 yards and two touchdowns as No. 15 Florida routed Kentucky 48-10 on Saturday night for the Gators' 25th straight win in the series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Florida starts off slow before walloping Kentucky

events.name: Rice Owls at Baylor Bears

headlines.description: Robert Griffin III threw five touchdown passes and ran for another score to lead No. 17 Baylor to a 56-31 victory over Rice on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin hits 5 different WRs for TDs in Baylor win

events.name: UTEP Miners at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: B.J. Daniels threw for 202 yards and ran for 130 more, leading No. 18 South Florida to a 52-24 victory over UTEP on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: USF rides roughshod over undermanned UTEP

events.name: Portland State Vikings at TCU Horned Frogs

headlines.description: TCU scored three touchdowns in a span of 1:18 just before halftime, two on passes by Casey Pachall, and Waymon James ran 65 yards for a score on the first play of the second half as the No. 20 Horned Frogs won 55-13 over Portland State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU uses first-half explosion to roll Portland St.

events.name: San Diego State Aztecs at Michigan Wolverines

headlines.description: Quarterback Denard Robinson ran for three scores in the first half to give No. 22 Michigan a three-touchdown lead and finished with a season-high 200 yards rushing, helping the Wolverines beat San Diego State 28-7.

events.name: USC Trojans at Arizona State Sun Devils

headlines.description: Arizona St. 43, No. 23 Southern Cal 22
headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall's 3 TDs lead Arizona State past USC

events.name: Western Michigan Broncos at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: Troy Pollard rushed for a career-high 133 yards and No. 24 Illinois needed all three of Derek Dimke's field goals Saturday to survive Western Michigan 23-20 and improve to 4-0 for the first time since 1951.
headlines.shortLinkText: Illinois hangs on for best start in over 50 years

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets

headlines.description: Tevin Washington threw a long touchdown pass and ran for two scores, including a 5-yarder that gave No. 25 Georgia Tech a 35-28 victory over North Carolina on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ga. Tech staves off UNC late

events.name: Old Dominion Monarchs at Delaware Blue Hens
Central Michigan Chippewas at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Le'Veon Bell ran for 81 yards and three touchdowns -- all in the first half -- to lead Michigan State to a 45-7 victory over in-state rival Central Michigan on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bell's 3 TDs lead way as Michigan St. routs CMU

events.name: Toledo Rockets at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description:
Syracuse cornerback Kevyn Scott made an 
interception in the end zone on the first play of overtime, Ross Krautman kicked four field goals, including the 27-yard winner, and 
the Orange held off Toledo 33-30 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cuse wins in OT after an admitted blown call

events.name: Eastern Michigan Eagles at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: Matt McGloin threw for three touchdowns and Penn State welcomed coach Joe Paterno back to the sideline with a 34-6 win Saturday over Eastern Michigan.

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at Pittsburgh Panthers

headlines.description: Notre Dame quarterback Tommy Rees shrugged off a miserable first three quarters to hit tight end Tyler Eifert for a 6-yard touchdown with less than 7 minutes to go and lift the Fighting Irish to a 15-12 win over Pittsburgh on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irish top Pitt on late TD strike

three touchdowns and Iowa cruised past Louisiana-Monroe 45-17 on
Saturday.

events.name: Georgia Bulldogs at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Aaron Murray completed 17 of 26 passes for 268 yards and two touchdowns and Georgia beat Mississippi 27-13 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Efficient Murray directs Georgia past Mississippi

events.name: Temple Owls at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Bernard Pierce set a school record with five rushing touchdowns, and Temple built a 31-point halftime lead in a stunning 38-7 rout of Maryland on Saturday.

Chase Rettig threw for three touchdowns and Boston

events.name: Colorado Buffaloes at Ohio State Buckeyes

events.name: UCLA Bruins at Oregon State Beavers
